t%20of%20the%20sentence%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20bury%20it%20in%20the%20far%20right%20side%20of%20a%20sentence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc6abc27-d17c-4969-b2bd-c2182a22acb2%5C%22%3ELearn%20the%20language%20of%20hiring%20managers%20in%20your%20industry%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20in%20especially%20handy%20when%20considering%20a%20career%20change%20and%20trying%20to%20describe%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvaluable-transferrable-skills-of-the-future-2013-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransferrable%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20new%20industry%2C%20according%20to%20Santoriello.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20write%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20toward%20the%20new%20industry%2C%20you%20want%20to%20use%20the%20industry%20specific%20language%2C%26quot%3B%20Santoriello%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20about%20showing%20them%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0not%20telling%2C%20showing%20them%20%E2%80%94%20that%20you%20understand%20how%20your%20skill%20transfers%20and%20use%20that%20language%20to%20support%20that.%20It%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20the%2015%20years%20you've%20spent%20in%20tech%20aren't%20relevant%20now%20that%20you%20want%20to%20go%20into%20medical%20research.%20There's%20probably%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20skill%20there%20that's%20relevant.%20We%20just%20need%20to%20formulate%20it%20and%20put%20it%20in%20the%20language%20that%20the%20new%20industry%20understands.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20noted%20that%20this%20is%20where%20a%20career%20coach%20really%20can%20help%2C%20but%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20describing%20the%20language%20of%20your%20chosen%20industry%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20%26quot%3Bplay%20with%20your%20best%20friend%20Google.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20I%20say%20play%2C%20I%20mean%20play%2C%20have%20fun.%20Go%20down%20rabbit%20holes%2C%20do%20the%20research%2C%20spend%20the%20time%20getting%20lost%20reading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticles%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Santoriello%20said.%20%26quot%3BJoin%20groups%20specific%20to%20where%20you%20want%20to%20go%20%E2%80%94%20both%20digital%20and%20face-to-face%20if%20that's%20your%20thing.%20Check%20out%20trade%20associations.%20There's%20so%20much%20information%20available%20today.%20When%20I'm%20working%20with%20my%20members%2C%20I%20say%20this%20to%20them%3A%20'It's%20scavenger%20hunt%20time.'%20Let's%20find%20the%20stuff%20and%20then%20compare%20it%20to%20what%20you%20already%20have%20in%20place%20so%20that%20we're%20presenting%20your%20best%20fit%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228df8fa8a-4215-4173-b030-4d44a764da15%5C%22%3EKeep%20your%20network%20simmering%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20wanted%20a%20forest%2C%20you%20needed%20to%20plant%20a%20tree%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20today%20would%20be%20OK%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Santoriello%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%2C%20she%20said%2C%20there's%20no%20bad%20time%20to%20be%20reaching%20out%20to%20friends%20and%20past%2C%20present%2C%20or%20prospective%20colleagues%20to%20set%20up%20informational%20interviews%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetwork-opportunities-work-job-careers-linkedin-social-media-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enetworking%20lunches%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20as%20human%20beings%2C%20people%20in%20the%20professional%20workplace%2C%20tend%20to%20not%20realize%20the%20value%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-importance-of-networking-2011-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20connections%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20not%20a%20place%20you%20want%20to%20stagnate%2C%26quot%3B%20Santoriello%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20be%20building%20your%20connection%20base%20regular